	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />ok, another dumb question, how to you look in the iNES header?  sorry im not very saavy with technical jargon.  thanks
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In the iNES header, there is a number equaling the amount of 8kb CHRROM banks in it.<br />If that number is zero, there is no CHROM so there is CHRAM.<br />Games that have both of them are very rare and particular cases tough (TQROM board, I think).</div>

		

		</td>
