	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The "header" of a file is simply the data at the beginning that is usually used to further identify the contents of the file. To look at the iNES header, you can use a "hex" editor, an editing program that displays the bytes of a file in hexadecimal (base 16) and allows editing. You'll also need to find a description of the iNES header format, the way that those bytes are interpreted.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

