		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />so which hex editor do you recommend, i have thingy32, but have no clue how it works.  is the iNES header the top line on the table?
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The "header" of a file is simply the data at the beginning that is usually used to further identify the contents of the file. To look at the iNES header, you can use a "hex" editor, an editing program that displays the bytes of a file in hexadecimal (base 16) and allows editing. You'll also need to find a description of the iNES header format, the way that those bytes are interpreted.</div>

		

